title: PNG to resettle refugees three years after Manus Island detention centre was reopened
text:
PNG to resettle refugees three years ... PNG to resettle refugees three years after Manus Island detention centre was reopened Next Story Prev Story 2 hrs ago Read more: ABC News 
TIM PALMER: Papua New Guinea has announced it will start to resettle detainees on Manus Island who have been found to be refugees. That announcement comes almost exactly three years after the then Rudd government reopened the centre to detain asylum seekers intercepted by Australia.   ABC News.
